ENTRY            C3102   20260120   20260312   20260312       C253
SUBENT        C3102001   20260120   20260312   20260312       C253
BIB                 13         22
TITLE      Production of no-carrier added 67Cu
AUTHOR     (S.Mirzadeh,L.F.Mausner,S.C.Srivastava)
REFERENCE  (J,ARI,37,29,1986)
           #doi:10.1016/0883-2889(86)90192-9
REL-REF    (O,12970001,S.Mirzadeh+,J,ARI,37,29,1986) Neutron data.
INSTITUTE  (1USABNL)
FACILITY   (LINAC,1USABNL) BLIP.
INC-SPECT  The average beam current was about 2 microA.
DETECTOR   (GELI) 50 cc detector.
SAMPLE     Foils of Zn (disk, r = 2.7 cm, 100-400 mg/cm2
           thickness) were wrapped in stainless steel foil
            (198 mg/cm2).
METHOD     (ACTIV,CHSEP) Foils of Zn were irradiated at the BLIP
           facility with protons of Ep ~ 190 MeV. After
           irradiation the target was dissolved in 10 mL of
           cont. HCl and 1 mL of cont. HNO3. The effective cross-
           section of natZn(p,2pxn)67Cu was measured at 200 MeV
           by irradiation of 120-l50 mg of natural Zn metal for
           10-20 min at the Chemistry Linac Irradiation Facility.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No details on sources of uncertainties.
MONITOR    (13-AL-27(P,X)11-NA-24,,SIG)
HISTORY    (20260120C) BP
